org.strongback.control

Interface Controller

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Requirable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    PIDController, TalonController
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SoftwarePIDController

    public interface Controller
extends Requirable
    A simple controller that can manage a component (typically a motor) based upon a desired target value and tolerance.
    See Also:
    PIDController

      • checkTolerance

        default boolean checkTolerance(double value)
        Determines whether the supplied value is within the tolerance of the target.
        Parameters:
        value - the proposed value
        Returns:
        true if the proposed value is within the tolerance of the target, or false otherwise

      • isWithinTolerance

        default boolean isWithinTolerance()
        Determines whether the input to the controller is currently within the tolerance of the target.
        Returns:
        true if the current value is within the tolerance of the target, or false otherwise

      • computeOutput

        boolean computeOutput()
        Calculate the next controller output. This usually involves reading one or more inputs and computing the output based upon a model of the system.
        Returns:
        true if the execution completed because it resulted in a value that is within the tolerance of the setpoint, or false if this controller is not enabled or has not yet reached the setpoint given the tolerance

      • reset

        Controller reset()
        Reset any error values stored from previous executions.
        Returns:
        this object so that methods can be chained; never null

      • hasExecutable

        default boolean hasExecutable()
        Return whether the Executable instance returned by executable() does anything useful. Software-based controllers may often return true, whereas many hardware-based controllers may return false.
        Returns:
        true if the executable() does useful work and enables the controller to operate continually and automatically, or false if the executable() does nothing.

      • executable

        Executable executable()
        Get the Executable instance that will continuously execute this controller to read inputs from the source and generate outputs to reach the target.

        If this is used, then this same controller should never be used with commands. This is not checked, so robot programs are responsible for ensuring this does not happen.

        Returns:
        the Executable object that can be registered with an Executor (typically Strongback's central executor); never null and always the same instance for this controller
